President Obama has declared a major disaster in the District of Columbia and authorized federal aid to assist in the recovery efforts from a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred in December 2009. The federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and protective measures. Hazard mitigation measures will also be funded. Regis Leo Phelan has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made if requested by the District of Columbia. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.